{"type":"message","id":"899888c8","parentId":"fc10db06","timestamp":"2026-03-05T04:03:39.365Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Based on the docs, I can see that to register a skill in openclaw.json, I need to use the `skills.entries` configuration. The docs mention:\n\n- Skills can be loaded from three places: bundled, managed/local (`~/.openclaw/skills`), and workspace (`<workspace>/skills`)\n- Extra skill folders can be added via `skills.load.extraDirs`\n- Per-skill config uses `skills.entries.<skillName>`\n\nLet me search for more specific info on `skills.entries` configuration.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7z17n5ntnxuf_1","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"maxChars":4000,"url":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/gateway/configuration-reference#skills.entries"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5:free","usage":{"input":1638,"output":154,"cacheRead":21588,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23380,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772683408339}}
